        "name": "Autara Lending",
        "version": "0.1.0",
        "spec": "0.1.0",
        "description": "Autara lending protocol. Native Arch program; instructions are Borsh-encoded as [1-byte AurataInstructionTag][payload]. Discriminators below are the tag enum's declaration-order indices (autara-lib/src/ixs/types.rs). All 20 instructions are covered. For create_market/update_config, the nested Pod config types (LtvConfig=48B, IFixedPoint=16B, OracleConfig=257B over Borsh; 264B in memory) are represented as opaque fixed-size u8 arrays so byte offsets stay exact while keeping the IDL small; the InterestRateCurveKind enum carries opaque variant payloads (Fixed=16B, Polyline=64B, Adaptive=16B)."
      },
